MM is completely right. The only way to get rid of an infected thread is to delete it. You can't edit it out. That pretty much means any poster has the ability to delete any thread they want gone. With HTML on, someone could plant a trap in any of the larger game threads and you would have no choice but to delete it. For that matter, someone could plant a trap in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EVERY</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> thread on the board in a matter of mins - Remember planting a trap is only limited by the time it takes to hit a submit button. RARELY does anyone ever plant one trap and leave.  <br>
<br>
And I do see HUGE HARM in something that brings down your system. Its not outside the realm of possiblity that a trap exist that would keep you from restarting your computer at all. Not to mention all the reasons MM listed.<br>
<br>
Also I don't see one thing that a general poster can do with HTML that you can't already do with BBcodes. Ezboard even has the 'center' BBcode installed which most message boards don't.<br>
